  "stimulus": "At time $t$, the position of a particle moving in the $xy$-plane is given by the parametric functions $(x(t),\\, y(t))$, where $\\dfrac{dx}{dt} = t^2 + \\sin(3t^2)$. The graph of $y$, consisting of three line segments, is shown in the figure above. At $t = 0$, the particle is at position $(5, 1)$.",
